HEADWORD: Saponul
<hw>Sap"o*nul</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>saponule</ets>, fr. L. <ets>sapo</ets>, <ets>-onis</ets>,
soap.]</ety> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld> <def>A soapy mixture obtained by
treating an essential oil with an alkali; hence, any similar compound of
an essential oil.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>saponule</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

